My husband really liked this dish, so I gave it three forks even though I wasn't personally overwhelmed. I thought it had great flavor, but it was so ridiculously rich that I just couldn't stomach very much of it. I was also quite disappointed with the presentation, as the cheese clumps and curdles after baking, making the whole dish look rather unappetizing. It's somewhat better after it rests for the ten minutes the recipe calls for, but I would certainly never consider it worthy for entertaining. If I ever made it again (and I doubt I will), I'd try substituting the heavy cream for half and half.

